in the reality of America Roosevelt was regarded as a loathsome creature ru=
ining the country. John Adams said at the time that one-third of the countr=
y was for the revolution, one third were loyalists and one third didn=E2=80=
=99t care.&nbsp; He summed up the reality of cyclical change. Those who dem=
